8:
Feels like déjà vu, huh? 
Me, catching you practicing in secret... 
Is something wrong? You're looking at
me funny.
11:
...Are you afraid? To keep dancing, I
mean.
18:
That would explain why I'm
hesitating.
21:
But I know I need to keep going
somehow.
25: Yeah... I know what that's like.
29:
Hey, Stella. Remember how we
danced before? Take my hands.
32:
It's okay to tune your thoughts out.
Forget all of that.
35:
Just listen to the music... Take in
your breathing and the beating of
your heart... And let go.
38:
Feel yourself melt away. Lose
yourself in whatever you want... In
the breeze flowing around you, or
the emotions you're drowning in...
46: Then, once again, you can forget—
52:
Stella is not a dancer. Don't force her
down that path.
55:
...If you want to teach her how to
dance, do it some other way.
66:
No one is more qualified than you. 
I still remember how beautiful you
looked when you danced with the
moon that day—
70:
I've told you already. I don't dance.
Not anymore.
77: Did you want to dance with Elise?
82:
Now that you bring it up... 
I guess I did. 
I'm not very good at noticing
what I want...
86:
Sorry, Stella. That wasn't a good
performance from me. Next time, 
I promise I'll teach you properly!
91:
You don't need to apologize. 
I learned plenty.
95:
What you said earlier... You
reminded me that I also need to
push forward somehow.
99: Stella, mind coming with me for a bit?
106:
Sonia Therese takes the stage! Like
a shooting star, with the wind at my
feet, I'll dazzle and charm!
116:
What about you two? Got any
compliments for me?
121: O-oh, um, yeah, that was great.
126:
You know you're playing right into
her hands, right?
131: I know! I'm doing my best, okay?
135:
Guess some things never change.
All right, spill. Why go out of your
way to change your outfit?
138: I doubt you did it to impress us.
142:
I sure didn't. I was actually thinking
of bringing Stella with me on a trip
back home.
145:
Considering everyone and their
mothers must've heard of the
Floating Lotus by now, I figured a
change of clothes might help
disguise me.
149:
In that case, you should bring some
bodyguards along too.
153:
I was just thinking that. Can't have
Stella getting hurt on my watch,
after all. So how about it? We could
MAYBE disguise Nimbus somehow—
158:
There's no way you're gonna be able
to hide the Hellcat of the Dunes.
162:
Well, it was worth a shot. Guess 
I have no choice but to count on 
you, Elise!
167:
As if I would let you leave me
behind. Wherever you and Stella go,
I'll follow.
174:
I've got some other stuff to prep, so
I'll catch you later!
179:
Sorry, Alk, but could you tag along?
I'd feel better with your blade at our
side.
183:
Of course I'll help. But... are you sure
about going? Especially considering
where you two came from...
187:
An awful place like that hasn't
changed much since you left, I bet.
192:
Like a bad scar that never fades...
But if Sonia's going, then I don't have
a choice.
199:
Whoa... Who knew all this sand was
hiding a place like this?
207:
You do remember we don't have a
hometown to return to, don't you?
210:
They took everything from us—even
our names. Where are you planning
on going on this trip "home"?
217:
Just the name brings back
memories, doesn't it? That's where
everything began for me... 
My birthplace, you could say.
221:
You'll protect me the whole way
there, won't you, Elise?
229:
I sure am. You should know that by
now.
